  "description": "<p>\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201605/831276e7873e40c389bb947da2a6cee1.jpg\" /></p>\n<p>\n\t<span style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\">之前两篇文章我们介绍了元音之间连读的两种情况：</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p773064/\" target=\"_blank\">用/j/连读元音</a></p>\n<p>\n\t<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p774202/\" target=\"_blank\">用/w/连读元音</a></p>\n<p>\n\t本文我们接着学习元音间连读的第三种情况：</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>Linking the vowels with a slight /r/ sound<br />\n\t用轻微的/r/连读元音</strong></p>\n<p align=\"left\">\n\t<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p775392\" title=\"点击获得更好的阅读体验\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_video.gif\" /></a></p>\n<p align=\"left\">\n\t当前后两个单词的末、首音节分别都是元音，而且前面的元音是/a:/, /ɔ:/, /ɜ:/或/ə/结尾的（比如 /ə/, /uə/, /eə/, /ɪə/等），在后面单词的元音前面加一个微弱的/r/音，把两个词连接起来。比如，far away和for us。</p>\n<p align=\"left\">\n\t这里用于连读的/r/的发音比在单词中音节起始处的/r/要轻微的多，舌头只是轻快地弹一下。比如get rid of, hear it两处的/r/是有明显差别的，应用的时候要注意区分。</p>\n<p align=\"left\">\n\t其实在中文里也有这种r的连读哦，在带了儿化音的字后面就会出现了。比如&ldquo;去哪儿啊？&rdquo;会在啊的前面加个r的音，大家想想看，有木有？</p>\n<p align=\"left\">\n\t<img src=\"http://i2.w.hjfile.cn/doc/201605/b4507a301f68451f91716fc161c6186f.gif\" style=\"line-height: 1.8em;\" />【情景对话】</p>\n<p align=\"left\">\n\t<a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p775392\" title=\"点击获得更好的阅读体验\"><img src=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/2009/images/rss_video.gif\" /></a></p>\n<p align=\"left\">\n\tIt's <u>four o'clock</u> in the afternoon. John is showing Mary around the company.<br />\n\tJohn: <u>Here is </u>the meeting room.<br />\n\tMary: Is this <u>where I</u> had my interview?<br />\n\tJohn: Could be.<br />\n\tMary: And&hellip;<u>where is </u>the toilet?<br />\n\tJohn:&nbsp;That <u>door over </u>there leads to the ladies&rsquo;.</p>\n<p align=\"left\">\n\tfou<span style=\"color: #f00;\">r o</span>'clock&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; /ˌfɔː <span style=\"color: #f00;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">r</span>ə</span>ˈklɒk/<br />\n\th<span style=\"color: #f00;\">ere i</span>s&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; /ˈhɪə <span style=\"font-size: 12px;\"><span style=\"color: #f00;\">r</span><span style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><span style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"color: #f00;\">ɪ</span>z</span>/</span></span><br />\n\twh<span style=\"color: #f00;\">ere I</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; /weə <span style=\"color: #f00;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">r</span>aɪ</span>/<br />\n\twh<span style=\"color: #f00;\">ere i</span>s&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; /ˈweə <span style=\"color: #f00;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">r</span>ɪz</span>/<br />\n\td<span style=\"color: #f00;\">oor o</span>ver&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; /ˈdɔ: <span style=\"color: #f00;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px;\">r</span>əʊ</span>və/&nbsp;</p>\n<p align=\"left\">\n\t以下这几段视频，节选自牛津大学商务英语教学课程，朋友们可以体会一下连读的实战技巧：<br />\n\t</p>\n<p align=\"left\">\n\t1. Okay, good morning everyone. Thank you very much for being <u>here on</u> time. We've got a lot to do today, so let's let started.<br />\n\t2. Now you all know why I&rsquo;ve called this meeting. Sales figures <u>for our</u> region are down. We need to address this as soon as we can.<br />\n\t3. But do you know why? Do the customers say why they don&rsquo;t like <u>our offers</u>? I personally feel that this is vital information.<br />\n\t4. Our products are competitive&hellip; So they&rsquo;re not getting <u>better offers</u> from the competition? I don&rsquo;t think so.</p>\n<p align=\"left\">\n\t<strong>以上加r的连读技巧掌握了吗？下一篇我们将介绍&ldquo;r连读&rdquo;的高能版哦~~敬请期待！</strong></p>\n<p style=\"font-size: 12px; color: #999999;\">\n\t声明：本文系沪江英语原创内容，转载请注明出处。</p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p775392/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p775392\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 styl